1) PRESENT CONTINUOUS (-ING)
******************************************

Uso: acciones ahora.

I am working.
She is studying.
They are playing.

Reglas:
work ‚Üí working
make ‚Üí making
run ‚Üí running
sit ‚Üí sitting


--------------------------------------------------

2) PAST SIMPLE (-ED + IRREGULARES)
******************************************

Regulares:
work ‚Üí worked
study ‚Üí studied
live ‚Üí lived

Irregulares:
go ‚Üí went
eat ‚Üí ate
see ‚Üí saw
have ‚Üí had
do ‚Üí did
make ‚Üí made
buy ‚Üí bought
take ‚Üí took
get ‚Üí got

Negativa:
I didn't go.

Pregunta:
Did you go?


--------------------------------------------------

3) WH QUESTIONS
******************************************

What
Which
Where
Who
Why
When
How

Where are you going?
Why did she leave?
Which color do you prefer?


--------------------------------------------------

4) PREPOSITIONS OF PLACE
******************************************

In = dentro
On = encima (superficie)
Under = debajo
Behind = detr√°s
In front of = delante de
Next to = al lado de
Between = entre (2 cosas)
Above = arriba (sin tocar)
Below = debajo (sin tocar)
Across from = enfrente de
Near = cerca de
Far from = lejos de

Ejemplos:

The cat is under the table.
The school is across from the bank.
The ball is behind the box.
She is standing in front of the door.
The lamp is above the table.


--------------------------------------------------

5) PREPOSITIONS OF MOVEMENT
******************************************

To = hacia
From = desde
Into = hacia dentro
Out of = hacia fuera
Onto = hacia encima
Off = quitar de
Through = a trav√©s de
Around = alrededor de
Across = cruzando

Ejemplos:

She is going to school.
He walked into the room.
The cat jumped onto the table.
They ran through the park.


--------------------------------------------------

6) THERE IS / THERE ARE
******************************************

There is a book.
There are two cars.


--------------------------------------------------

7) SOME / ANY
******************************************

Some (afirmativa)
Any (negativa/pregunta)


--------------------------------------------------

8) CAN / CAN‚ÄôT
******************************************

